## 2.Open playlist.txt in read mode (r) and display each song name on a separate line in the console.

```c
#include <stdio.h>

int main()
{
    FILE *fp;
    char song[100];

    fp = fopen("playlist.txt", "r");

    if (fp == NULL)
    {
        printf("File not found!\n");
        return 1;
    }

    while (fgets(song, sizeof(song), fp) != NULL)
    {
        printf("%s", song);
    }

    fclose(fp);

    return 0;
}
```

**Output (Example):**

```text
Tum Hi Ho
Kesariya
Believer
```

